NAME
    gcloud alpha resource-manager org-policies set-policy - set Organization
        Policy

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha resource-manager org-policies set-policy POLICY_FILE
        [--folder=FOLDER_ID] [--organization=ORGANIZATION_ID]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Sets an Organization Policy associated with the specified resource
    from a file that contains the JSON or YAML encoded Organization Policy.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     POLICY_FILE
        JSON or YAML file with the Organization Policy.

FLAGS
     --folder=FOLDER_ID
        Folder ID for Org Policies.

     --organization=ORGANIZATION_ID
        Organization ID for Org Policies.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

EXAMPLES
    The following command sets an Organization Policy for a constraint on
    project foo-project from file /tmp/policy.yaml:

        $ gcloud alpha resource-manager org-policies set-policy \
            --project=foo-project /tmp/policy.yaml

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. Usually,
    users of ALPHA commands and flags need to apply for access, agree to
    applicable terms, and have their projects whitelisted. Contact Google or
    sign up on a product's page for ALPHA access. Product pages can be found at
    https://cloud.google.com/products/. This variant is also available:

        $ gcloud beta resource-manager org-policies set-policy

